4}}</ref>\n*[[K. Kelappan]] \u2013 a.k.a. Kerala Gandhi, freedom fighter, founder of the [[Nair Service Society]]\n\n==Military personnel==\n*[[Maj Gen]] [[V.N. Parameswaran Pillai]] - General Officer Commanding (GOC), [[Travancore Nair Brigade]].\n* [[Lt General]] [[Kunhiraman Palat Candeth|K P Candeth]]<ref>BJP today, Volume 12. Page:20, Column:3</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CBK7DgAAQBAJ&pg=PT46&dq=K.P+Candeth+Nayar&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiI3bTZ5MriAhWI4HMBHcB4AxIQ6AEILjAB#v=onepage&q=K.P%20Candeth%20Nayar&f=false|title=Themes of Glory: Indian Artillery in War|last=Khullar|first=Darshan|date=2017-05-15|publisher=|year=|isbn=9789385563973|location=|pages=46|language=en}}</ref> \u2013 Lieutenant General in the Indian Army during Indo-Pak war\n*[[Sandeep Unnikrishnan]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8LjjDAAAQBAJ&pg=PT146&dq=Nair+caste+ashoka+chakra&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjT18C1577bAhUD6Y8KHSCHBJgQ6AEIJjAA#v=onepage&q=Nair%20caste%20ashoka%20chakra&f=false|title=Ashoka Chakra Recipients|last=Aggarwal|first=Rashmi|date=101|publisher=Prabhat Prakashan|language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Lakshmi Sahgal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/a-matriarchal-home-to-many-illustrious-daughters-of-india/989510/|title=A matriarchal home to many illustrious daughters of India - Indian Express|date=2012-08-17|website=Archive.indianexpress.com|accessdate=2016-02-24}}</ref> \u2013 freedom fighter of the Azad Hind Army\n* [[ Major General Jai Shanker Menon ]] \u2013 Head of Mission and Force Commander of United Nations Disengagement Observer Force\n* [[ Air Marshal Narayan Menon ]] \u2013 Air Officer-in-Charge (Personnel), Air Headquarters (1999\u20132004)\n*[[Neelakantan Jayachandran Nair|Colonel Neelakantan Jayachandran Nair]] \u2013One of the most decorated officer of the Indian Army, as the only serviceman to have been awarded both the highest ([[Ashoka Chakra (military decoration)|Ashoka Chakra]]) and second highest ([[Kirti Chakra]]) awards for gallantry.\n*[[K. Vijay Kumar|K.Vijay Kumar]] - He was the Chief of the Special Task Force of Tamil Nadu that was involved in the death of the [[Veerappan]] during Operation Cocoon of 2004.\n\n==Scientists==\n*[[M. G. K. Menon]]\n*[[G. Madhavan Nair ]]\n*[[K. Radhakrishnan]]\n*[[Radhika Nair ]]\n*[[G. Balakrish Nair]]\n*[[Vijayan Nair]]\n\n==Industrialists/Business Leaders==\n*[[Cheril Krishna Menon]]  - Behzad Group, Qatar\n*[[P. N. C. Menon]] -Sobha developers\n*[[B. Ravi Pillai|Ravi Pillai]] -R.P Group\n*[[C. P. Krishnan Nair|CP Krishnan Nair]] - Leela group\n*[[Rajan Pillai]] - Former CFO of Britania Group\n*[[Rajeev Chandrasekhar]] -Founder of BPL Mobile also the chairman of Jupiter Capital owned Asianet News \n*[[E. Sreedharan]] - Chairman of DMC also known as The Metro Man \n*[[Sashi Kumar]] - Founder of Asianet \n*[[Atlas Ramachandran]] - Businessman\n\n== Journalists, Cartoonists and Radio / TV News Professionals ==\n*[[Chengalathu Kunhirama Menon]]\n*[[Kutty (cartoonist)]]\n*[[K. Shankar Pillai]]\n*[[Appan Menon]]\n*[[C. Karunakara Menon]]\n\n== Arts & Literature ==\n* [[Jayan]]\n* [[Bharath Gopi]]\n* [[Madhu]]\n* [[M. N. Nambiar]]\n*[[Prathapachandran]]\n* [[Nedumudi Venu]]\n* [[Suresh Gopi]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Philip|first=Shaju|title=Kerala actor Suresh Gopi snubbed by Hindu Nair leader|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/kerala-actor-suresh-gopi-snubbed-by-hindu-nair-leader/|accessdate= 28 December 2016|work=[[The Indian Express]]|location=Kerala|date=27 June 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Adoor Bhasi]]\n*[[Thoppil Bhasi]]\n*[[Adoor Gopalakrishnan]]\n*[[Padmarajan]]\n*[[G. K. Pillai (actor)|G.K Pillai]]\n* [[Dileep]]\n* [[Mohanlal]]\n* [[Priyadarshan]]\n*[[Shankar (actor)|Shankar]]\n*[[Major Ravi]]\n*[[Revathy Kalamandhir|G.Suresh Kumar]]\n*[[Gautham Menon]]\n*[[Ashokan (actor)|Ashokan]]\n*[[Raghuvaran]]\n*[[Shaji Kailas]]\n*[[Renji Panicker|Renji Paniker]]\n*[[Viji Thampi]]\n*[[Vinayan]]\n*[[Rajasenan]]\n*[[Ranjith