{"title_page": "Anadi Mishra", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\nAnadi Mishra is an Indian singer. He sings [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] folk, sufi and urban music. Mishra is associated with [[T-Series]], White Hill Music, Crown Records<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/music/punjabi/latest-punjabi-song-sawaal-sung-by-anadi-mishra/videoshow/70462404.cms|title=Latest Punjabi Song 'Sawaal' Sung By Anadi Mishra {{!}} Punjabi Video Songs|website=The Times of India|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>, Speed Records and P-Tunes<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCi2LnkG8ek1LlKYhVuOr-3Q|title=Anadi Mishra \u2013 Topic|via=YouTube|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestatesman.com/inspiration-hub/anadi-mishra-manifold-talents-field-music-1502871371.html|title=Anadi Mishra has manifold talents in the field of music|date=2020-03-29|website=The Statesman|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref>. Anadi acted in a TV Commercial for world cup 2019<ref name=\":2\" />.\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Anadi Mishra\n| image              = Anadimishramusic.jpg\n| birth_name         = {{Birth date and age |1993|09|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[jalandhar]], Punjab, India\n| occupation         = Singer\n| net_worth          = $1.3&nbsp;million\n| mother             = Dr. Amita Mishra\n| father             = Dr. Arun Mishra\n| website            = www.anadimishra.com\n| Genre              = [[Sufi]], [[romantic]], [[sad]], dance and [[folk]]\n}}\n\n== Personal life ==\nAnadi started his career at the early age of 9. He is awarded as the Youngest \u201cA\u201d Graded Singer of India by the Central Indian Government (Delhi). He completed his studies from - Apeejay School (jalandhar) and the higher studies from Apeejay college of fine arts (jalandhar) He is classically trained by his Grandfather - Dr. Shankar lal mishra (disciple of Ustad Amir Khan Saheb) of Indore Gharana of music and his Father - Dr. Arun Mishra. Anadi Mishra was born in Jalandhar on 21 September 1993<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latestly.com/lifestyle/meet-anand-mishra-the-lifeline-of-punjab-music-industry-1306096.html|title=Meet Anadi Mishra \u2013 The Lifeline of Punjab Music Industry {{!}} \ud83d\udecd\ufe0f LatestLY|date=31 October 2019|website=LatestLY|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> and holds the Highest Degree in the field of Music - PH.D (Doctor of Philosophy), M.A (Music Vocal) Gold Medalist, B.M.M (Bachelor's in Multi Media). He was born in Jalandhar, but splits most of his time amongst [[Chandigarh]], Punjab and [[Mumbai]]. Mishra's relative [[Sugandha Mishra]] is a Tv artist<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/archive/maintaining-rich-legacy-of-music-art-culture-424985|title=Maintaining rich legacy of music, art & culture|last=Service|first=Tribune News|website=Tribuneindia News Service|language=en|accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref><!-- WP:RS needed; removed link to WP-->.\n\n==Awards<ref name=\":0\" />==\n{{Awards table|3}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2012\u201313\n| Best Singer\n| Nation youth festival of India\n| {{Won}}\n|\n| <ref name=\":2\" />\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2013\u201314\n| Best Singer\n| Nation youth festival of India\n| {{Won}}\n|\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2014\u201315\n| Best Singer\n| Nation youth festival of India\n| {{Won}}\n|\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| Best Singer\n| Maneka Sanjay Gandhi Awards\n| {{won}}\n|\n|<!-- WP:RS needed-->\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2016\n| Best Singer\n| PTC Music Awards\n| {{Nominated}}\n|\n|<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.openthenews.com/anadi-mishra-the-lifeline-of-punjab-music-industry/|title=ANADI MISHRA: THE LIFELINE OF PUNJAB MUSIC INDUSTRY|first=|website=theopennews|language=en|accessdate=2019-12-04}}</ref>\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n==Discography==\nRabb da deedar<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Rabb-Da-Deedar/dp/B01N7JU7H4|title=Rabb Da Deedar |website=www.amazon.com|accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nSawaal\n\nAkhiyan De Hanju\n\nQueen Of Heart\n\nDoli Vs Athru\n\nJee na Sakaan\n\nKadi aa mil sanwal\n\n<br />\n\n== References ==\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\nAnadi Mishra is an Indian singer. He sings [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] folk, sufi and urban music. Mishra is associated with [[T-Series]], White Hill Music, Crown Records<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/music/punjabi/latest-punjabi-song-sawaal-sung-by-anadi-mishra/videoshow/70462404.cms|title=Latest Punjabi Song 'Sawaal' Sung By Anadi Mishra {{!}} Punjabi Video Songs|website=The Times of India|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>, Speed Records and P-Tunes<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCi2LnkG8ek1LlKYhVuOr-3Q|title=Anadi Mishra \u2013 Topic|via=YouTube|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestatesman.com/inspiration-hub/anadi-mishra-manifold-talents-field-music-1502871371.html|title=Anadi Mishra has manifold talents in the field of music|date=2020-03-29|website=The Statesman|language=en-US|accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref>. Anadi acted in a TV Commercial for world cup 2019<ref name=\":2\" />.\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Anadi Mishra\n| image              = Anadimishramusic.jpg\n| birth_name         = {{Birth date and age |1993|09|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[jalandhar]], Punjab, India\n| occupation         = Singer\n| net_worth          = $1.3&nbsp;million\n| mother             = Dr. Amita Mishra\n| father             = Dr. Arun Mishra\n| website            = www.anadimishra.com\n| Genre              = [[Sufi]], [[romantic]], [[sad]], dance and [[folk]]\n}}\n\n== Personal life ==\nAnadi started his career at the early age of 9. He is awarded as the Youngest \u201cA\u201d Graded Singer of India by the Central Indian Government (Delhi). He completed his studies from - Apeejay School (jalandhar) and the higher studies from Apeejay college of fine arts (jalandhar) He is classically trained by his Grandfather - Dr. Shankar lal mishra (disciple of Ustad Amir Khan Saheb) of Indore Gharana of music and his Father - Dr. Arun Mishra. Anadi Mishra was born in Jalandhar on 21 September 1993<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latestly.com/lifestyle/meet-anand-mishra-the-lifeline-of-punjab-music-industry-1306096.html|title=Meet Anadi Mishra \u2013 The Lifeline of Punjab Music Industry {{!}} \ud83d\udecd\ufe0f LatestLY|date=31 October 2019|website=LatestLY|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> and holds the Highest Degree in the field of Music - PH.D (Doctor of Philosophy), M.A (Music Vocal) Gold Medalist, B.M.M (Bachelor's in Multi Media). He was born in Jalandhar, but splits most of his time amongst [[Chandigarh]], Punjab and [[Mumbai]]. Mishra's relative [[Sugandha Mishra]] is a Tv artist<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/archive/maintaining-rich-legacy-of-music-art-culture-424985|title=Maintaining rich legacy of music, art & culture|last=Service|first=Tribune News|website=Tribuneindia News Service|language=en|accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref><!-- WP:RS needed; removed link to WP-->.\n\n==Awards<ref name=\":0\" />==\n{{Awards table|3}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2012\u201313\n| Best Singer\n| Nation youth festival of India\n| {{Won}}\n|\n| <ref name=\":2\" />\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2013\u201314\n| Best Singer\n| Nation youth festival of India\n| {{Won}}\n|\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2014\u201315\n| Best Singer\n| Nation youth festival of India\n| {{Won}}\n|\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| Best Singer\n| Maneka Sanjay Gandhi Awards\n| {{won}}\n|\n|<!-- WP:RS needed-->\n\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2016\n| Best Singer\n| PTC Music Awards\n| {{Nominated}}\n|\n|<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.openthenews.com/anadi-mishra-the-lifeline-of-punjab-music-industry/|title=ANADI MISHRA: THE LIFELINE OF PUNJAB MUSIC INDUSTRY|first=|website=theopennews|language=en|accessdate=2019-12-04}}</ref>\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n==Discography==\nRabb da deedar<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Rabb-Da-Deedar/dp/B01N7JU7H4|website=www.amazon.com|accessdate=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nSawaal\n\nAkhiyan De Hanju\n\nQueen Of Heart\n\nDoli Vs Athru\n\nJee na Sakaan\n\nKadi aa mil sanwal\n\n<br />\n\n== References ==\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDiscography:Added title to ref", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anadi_Mishra"}
